comments:
I ran into the same exception using the I20050624 I-build.  I believe the 
earlier code above is from I20050603 and no longer compiles because 
IVirtualComponent no longer extends IVirtualContainer.  However, I found that 
the following code throws the same exception in I20050624 when run with a 
freshly created J2EE Web Project:

IVirtualComponent mod = flexProj.getComponent("webapp_name");
IVirtualFolder root = mod.getRootFolder();
IVirtualResource [] resArray = root.getResources("");
for (int i = 0; i < resArray.length; i++) {
    IResource res = resArray[i].getUnderlyingResource();
}

This code has the same issue with getFolder() that the earlier code does.

The code I had that was similar to that above no longer behaves the same as it 
did in M4, so it is no longer useful to me.  However, regardless of its 
usefulness, I wouldn't expect it to throw an exception.  There may be other 
more useful scenarios that might have the same problem with getFolder().
